# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
For a Black colored coordinate it can cover at max 4 blocks only, so we will see 4 blocks for each coordinate element, while taking care that the block is not previously visited

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1) First Put All coordinates in a set named "black" and an empty set "s", then traverse coordinates
2) For each coordinate[x,y], check all 4 blocks(at max) if a block is not previously visited(we use set "s" for it) we count number of black coordinate(using set "black") in a block then update it in "ans"(answer vector)
3) For block with 0 black coordinate preset we update "ans" at the end. i.e ans[0]=(m-1)*(n-1)-(blocks with 1-4 black coordinate).
**As mxn grid has (m-1)*(n-1) => 2x2 blocks

Note: We can also use unordered_set but you have to define Hash Function for itbecause by default, C++ doesn't allow us to create an unordered set of pairs directly but one can pass a hash function to the unordered set container. 

# Complexity
- Time complexity:(coordinates.length*log(coordinates.length))
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:O(coordinates.length)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

