class Solution {
public:
    int solve(int left , int right){
        int bit1 = 0;
        int bit2 = 0;
        while(left > 0){
            left /= 2;
            bit1++;
        }
        while(right > 0){
            right /= 2;
            bit2++;
        }
        if(bit1 < bit2) return 0;
        return (1 << bit1) - 1;
    }
    int rangeBitwiseAnd(int left, int right) {
        return solve(left , right);
    }
};
```
`bit1` and `bit2` should be the number of bits required to represent `left` and `right` respectively. So, instead of using `log2()`, I calculate the number of bits using repeated division by 2. The bitwise AND operation between `left` and `right` returns the bitwise AND of all the numbers in the given range

