# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Basically This Question Try to Test Pattern Finding Skill.
This Problem has 2 things two Consider.
1) Firstly We Divide n by 7 ( as Week is of  Days ) So that We get Value Which Indicates that Total Number of Weeks need to Consider in Final Answer.

2) Now We Do n%7 which gives answer between 0 to 6 which indicates Remaining Days after Step 1. So We need To calculate Sum of Savings for That n%7 days Separately.

As Sum of

Week 1 : 28
Week 2 : 35
Week 3 : 42
Week 4 : 49
Week 5 : 56
and so on...
 Indicates Pattern that We only need How many Whole Week Need to Consider in answer and that We got in Step 1.
So add 28+35+.. upto n/7 terms


Now , In Step 2 , We need to consider Saving For Remainig Days which is n%7.
Suppose Rem Day is B then B*(B+1)/2 Will be Saving at B day of Week 1.We know that we have n/7 week so n/7*b will be added to B*(B+1)/2
.This is Final answer of Step 2.

3) Add Both answer of Step 1 and Step 2.



